Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Space Sensors and Actuators Market

The space sensors and actuators market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 18.3% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on space sensors and actuators market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The expansion of the automotive sector globally is escalating the growth of space sensors and actuators market.

The space sensor refers to the equipment that assists in measuring, indicating and detecting specific physical quantities such as light, moisture, pressure, and heat among others. The actuator is defined as a device that helps in achieving physical movements by transforming energy into mechanical force.

The increase in demand for wireless sensors in various space applications acts as one of the major factor driving the growth of the space sensors and actuators market. The continuous development of radiation-hardened electro-optical space sensors, and significant investments by private firms leading to more space exploration missions accelerate the market growth. The increase in adoption of CMOS image sensors for Earth observation, and rise in popularity of small & smart actuators for space robotic missions and microsatellites further influence the market. Additionally, expansion of automotive sector, high focus on reducing cost of space sensors, growth of the heavy engineering industry, rapid urbanization and use of solar sensors for deep space missions positively affect the space sensors and actuators market. Furthermore, development of quantum sensors for space gravity and climate, Use of solar MEMS technology in new space projects and advancements in actuators for small satellites and launch vehicles extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, issues with sensor and actuator technology maturity for surface missions, and government policies related to spacecraft are expected to obstruct the market growth. Increased threat of radiation damage and corrosive atmospheres and complexity in design are projected to challenge the space sensors and actuators market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

